Case called for a plea and sentencing hearing and a restitution hearing.  Defendant David B Oldenburg in court with attorney Adam J. Schleis.  David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads guilty to count #1.  Court finds the defendant guilty of count #1.  Count #2 is dismissed and read in.  Stipulation between the parties for partial restitution amount of $20.48.  State calls witness, Victim V. D. sworn in, testified regarding the rest of the restitution requested.  Court makes oral ruling as to the remainder of the restitution requested.  Court orders restitution be set at $2824.87 total.  Victim makes statements.  

State makes recommendations.  Attorney Schleis makes statements.  Defendant makes statements. 
The Court Orders the Following:
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
100 Days Huber with STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.  (Credit - 1 days).  
Term of Probation: 1 Year may be transferred to Walworth County
Conditions of Probation:
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
No contact with victim or her residence or her son.   
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
No Use or Possession of illegal controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
Inform agent of all prescriptions;
Disclose to any physician in writing your probation conditions.  
Sign Medical Release for Agent;
Condition Time:  15 days Huber with  NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - STAYED to be used at the Agents discretion
Restitution: $2824.87 to be paid to V.D as a condition of probation.  
COSTS:  $253.00 to be paid as a condition of probation
DNA Surcharge: $200.00 to be paid as a condition of probation
DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
